Now I can show the literal wire shape. Both calls are built by `system_msg`/`user_msg` (`openrouter.rs:68-81`) → `{role, content}` objects, and passed to `chat_once` with the tools argument as `None` (`inject.rs:829`, `inject.rs:964`). So **both calls are exactly two messages, no tools array, single completion expected back.**

## SELECT (gate) call

```jsonc
// chat_once(client, key, select_model, msgs, None /*tools*/, max_tokens=300, turn=1)
messages = [
  {
    "role": "system",
    "content":
      // SELECT_PREAMBLE  (inject.rs:769-781)
      "You are a relevance gate for a coding assistant's context injector. ...\n"
      "- If NOTHING is directly relevant, output exactly: NOTHING_RELEVANT\n..."
      "\n\nCATALOG:\n"
      "- inject-subcommand — Inject subcommand — The per-prompt hook ...  [similar 0.71]\n"
      "- inject-pipeline-roles — ...\n"
      "- docs/wiki/foo.md — Foo — ...\n"
      // ...up to 150 lines...
      // then, only if recent non-empty:
      "\nRECENT CONVERSATION (background context):\n\n"
      "User: ...\n\nAssistant: ...\n\n"
  },
  {
    "role": "user",
    "content": "<the raw current prompt, input.prompt verbatim>"
  }
]
```

**Providing:** catalog (key — title — summary [— score]) + recent convo. **Asking:** newline-separated catalog keys, or the literal `NOTHING_RELEVANT`. No file contents, no tools.

## COMPILE call

```jsonc
// chat_once(client, key, compile_model, msgs, None /*tools*/, max_tokens=cfg, turn=2)
messages = [
  {
    "role": "system",
    "content":
      // COMPILE_PREAMBLE  (inject.rs:43-66)
      "You are a context compiler for an AI coding assistant (Claude Code). ...\n"
      "Output EXACTLY this shape:\nTITLE: <2-8 words ...>\n<cited facts ...>\n..."
      "\n\n"
      // context  (inject.rs:950-957), recent block only if non-empty:
      "RECENT CONVERSATION (background only):\n\nUser: ...\n\nAssistant: ...\n\n"
      "SOURCE DOCUMENTS (line-numbered; synthesize only what is relevant):\n\n"
      // render_guides_for_select  (inject.rs:905-915), one block per selected source:
      "=== source: ./docs/wiki/inject-subcommand.md ===\n"
      "   1| ---\n   2| title: Inject subcommand\n   3| ...\n  42| ...\n\n"
      "=== source: ./src/inject.rs ===\n   1| ...\n"
  },
  {
    "role": "user",
    "content": "<the raw current prompt, input.prompt verbatim>"
  }
]
```

**Providing:** full **line-numbered** content of the gate-selected files (`N| text`), each under a `=== source: ./relpath ===` header, plus recent convo. **Asking:** a `TITLE: …` line then synthesized prose where every claim carries an inline `(path:line)` citation — explicitly *not* an answer to the prompt.

## Notes on the shape

- **The user message is identical in both calls** — the raw `input.prompt`, never the `enriched_query`. All the actual material (catalog / sources / recent) rides in the `system` content.
- **No tools, no assistant/tool turns.** The `None` 5th arg to `chat_once` is the tools parameter (`inject.rs:829`, `964`); contrast with the tool-call helpers `assistant_tool_calls_msg`/`tool_result_msg` (`openrouter.rs:88-101`) which this path never uses. Single system+user → single text completion.
- **Ollama path is the same two-message shape** expressed via rig: `.preamble(preamble)` is the system content, `.prompt(current_prompt)` is the user message (`inject.rs:833-839`, `968-974`).
- **`turn`** is just a logging tag (1 = select, 2 = compile), not part of the wire payload.
